article.headline: Md.-Eastern Shore 80, Navy 72
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. -- Hillary Haley scored 20 points to lead Maryland-Eastern Shore to an 80-72 victory over Navy on Wednesday night. Navy took a 70-68 lead on Romeo Garcia's jumper with 5:03 left, but Maryland-Eastern Shore (3-5), which has won three straight games, scored the next 12 points for an 80-70 advantage with 3 seconds left. Mark Robertson hit a 3-pointer and Tim Burns hit all four of his free throw attempts in the final run. The Hawks, who entered the game shooting 60.1 percent from the free throw line, were 21-for-27 (77.8 percent) against Navy (4-6). Tyler Hines had 16 points and 12 rebounds, Kevin White scored 11 and Tim Burns added 10 points for Maryland-Eastern Shore. Neal Pitt and Sean Berry also added 10 rebounds each for the Hawks. Chris Harris scored 23 points and Jordan Sugars had 19 points and 14 rebounds for Navy, which shot 40 percent from the field (28-for-70).
